cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper utilizes machine learning methods to predict the effectiveness of growth mindset interventions in a nationwide experiment with over 10,000 students. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of complex relationships between student-level predictor variables and intervention outcomes, which could fall under the Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-categories. The paper also utilizes predictive models, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper has implications for the design of computer-administered interventions, which could fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
